headline: Oil’s Collapse Deepens Below $60 as China Hikes Tariffs on US
summary: (Bloomberg) -- Oil plunged to a four-year low as an intensifying trade war endangered energy demand, with a fresh wave of US and Chinese levies menacing the global economy.Brent futures tumbled below $60 a barrel for the first time since 2021 as natural gas, copper and other commodities also slid.
